    "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/decision/dr-cou1-noncannulated-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All three QoIs pass the pre-specified E/uval < 1.96 acceptance criterion. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required level. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 2 vs. required 3) is accepted given regulatory precedent for single-condition F1717 testing and the Medium model risk level. The UQ campaign documented in TR-NAG-2024-01 Section 6 provides confidence that dominant input parameters are identified and that prediction uncertainty is adequately bounded. Overall credibility is sufficient to support a Medium assurance level for this Class II device submission.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
